 W-184 resolved resonance parameter evaluation was done in the    7437 1451
energy range form 1e-5 eV to 10 keV with the SAMMY code[ref1].    7437 1451
Capture and transmission measurements for enriched W-184 and      7437 1451
natural tungsten were used in the evaluation. The measurements    7437 1451
were done at the Oak Ridge Linear Accelerator (ORELA)[ref2] and   7437 1451
at the Geel Linear Accelerator (GELINA), Belgium[ref3]. Neutron   7437 1451
transmission and capture data were measured in the energy range   7437 1451
from 20 eV to 10 keV.                                             7437 1451
 Thermal cross section[ref4] data available in the EXFOR library  7437 1451
were also used in the evaluation.                                 7437 1451
                                                                  7437 1451
 Resonance parameter covariance matrices were also obtained in    7437 1451
the SAMMY evaluation process in the energy region 1e-5 eV-10 keV. 7437 1451
The RML formalist (LRF=7) was used for the resonance parameters   7437 1451
and the compact formalism (LCOMP=2) for the covariance matrix.    7437 1451
