 CROSS-SECTION EVALUATION PROCEDURE                               7437 1451
                                                                  7437 1451
 Adopted procedure is based on careful theoretical                7437 1451
 analysis utilizing available experimental data and               7437 1451
 nuclear reaction model calculations.                             7437 1451
                                                                  7437 1451
 Available experimental data were interpreted  using              7437 1451
 nuclear reaction model code EMPIRE-2.19b35 by                    7437 1451
 M. Herman et al [He01, He02]. This code integrates               7437 1451
 into a single system a number of important modules               7437 1451
 and features:                                                    7437 1451
                                                                  7437 1451
 - Spherical and deformed Optical Model including                 7437 1451
   coupled-channels (ECIS03 by J. Raynal)                         7437 1451
 - Hauser-Feshbach statistical model including                    7437 1451
   HRTW width fluctuation correction                              7437 1451
 - Quantum-mechanical MSD TUL model (codes ORION &                7437 1451
   TRISTAN by H. Lenske), and MSC NVWY model                      7437 1451
 - Exciton model with angular momentum coupling                   7437 1451
   (code DEGAS by E. Betak and P. Oblozinsky) that                7437 1451
   represents a good approximation to the DSD model               7437 1451
 - Exciton model with Iwamoto-Harada cluster                      7437 1451
   emission and Kalbach systematic angular distr.                 7437 1451
   (code PCROSS by R.Capote et al)                                7437 1451
 - Complete gamma-ray cascade after emission of                   7437 1451
   each particle, including realistic treatment of                7437 1451
   discrete transitions                                           7437 1451
 - Access to OM segment of the RIPL-2 library [Ri03]              7437 1451
 - Built-in input parameter files, such as masses,                7437 1451
   level density, discrete levels, fission barriers               7437 1451
   and gamma strength functions  based on the RIPL-2              7437 1451
   library [Ri03]                                                 7437 1451
 - Automatic retrieval of experimental data from the              7437 1451
   EXFOR/CSISRS library                                           7437 1451
 - ENDF-6 formatting (code EMPEND by A. Trkov)                    7437 1451
   coupled to graphical presentation capabilities                 7437 1451
   (code ZVView by V. Zerkin) through the chain of                7437 1451
   PrePro codes by R. Cullen                                      7437 1451
 - Checking codes (CHECKR, FIZCON, PSYCHE)                        7437 1451
 - Support for NJOY                                               7437 1451
