RESONANCE COVARIANCE DATA (L. Leal, ORNL, Jan 2008)               7437 1451
                                                                  7437 1451
The procedure used to generate the resolved covariance data       7437 1451
with the SAMMY code is as follow:                                 7437 1451
 a) Retrieve best set of available resonance parameters.          7437 1451
 b) Convert the resonance parameters into the Reich-Moore form.   7437 1451
 c) Generate "experimental" cross sections for total, scattering, 7437 1451
    and capture cross sections with the NJOY code, for use as     7437 1451
    "experimental data" in SAMMY.                                 7437 1451
 d) Assign a global "experimental" uncertainty to the             7437 1451
    "experimental data." The uncertainties used were based on     7437 1451
    uncertainty in the thermal capture cross section and          7437 1451
    uncertainty in the capture resonance integrals.               7437 1451
 e) Run SAMMY code with the option to generate                    7437 1451
    resonance-covariances retroactively.                          7437 1451
 f) Convert the resonance-covariance results from SAMMY into      7437 1451
    the ENDF format for file 32 and MT=151.                       7437 1451
                                                                  7437 1451
The resulting resonance parameters and covariance were used in    7437 1451
the calculations of average cross sections and uncertainties.     7437 1451
The calculations were done with SAMMY, ERRORJ, and PUFF-IV codes. 7437 1451
The results of these three codes agreed very well.                7437 1451
